This suggests that we would only find a holographic description for
critical branes satisfying . Unlike in Einstein gravity, there
will be no extension to non-critical branes.

To sum up, we have found a condition that determines when a
holographic description will be valid for a brane moving in a black
hole bulk. This condition is satisfied for Einstein gravity,
regardless of the brane's position, or the value of the braneworld
cosmological constant. For Gauss-Bonnet gravity, the condition is far
more restrictive. It only holds for critical branes close to the AdS
boundary. We conclude that the holographic description shown in the
last section is the only one you can find for branes in  Gauss-Bonnet
gravity.

Cardy-Verlinde formulae  
The Cardy-Verlinde formula  for a CFT is the
generalisation to arbitrary dimensions of the well known Cardy
formula  for -dimensional CFTs. It relates the
entropy, , of the CFT, to its energy, , and Casimir energy,
. The Casimir energy can be thought of as providing  the
non-extensive part of the formula. In this paper, we will discuss the
local version of the Cardy-Verlinde formula for a CFT living on an FRW
brane.

We begin with the thermodynamic relation
E= T S-p V,
where ,  and  are the temperature, pressure and volume of the
CFT respectively.
If we introduce the following densities,
s=S V , E V ,
we can use the fact that  to rewrite the thermodynamic
relation in the following form,
d ds+d(1 Z^2 ),
where
(n-2)Z^2 2 (+ p-Ts).
We can think of  as describing the variation of  with
respect to the spatial curvature, . If the entropy and energy
were purely extensive,  would vanish.  will therefore
give the non-extensive part of the local Cardy-Verlinde formula.

In section , we showed that for a critical brane near
the AdS boundary, the dynamics is driven by a CFT that is dual to the
Gauss-Bonnet AdS black hole bulk. Eventually we will state the
Cardy-Verlinde formula for this CFT. However, first we will review the
form of the Cardy-Verlinde formula for a CFT that is dual to an AdS
black hole bulk in Einstein gravity.
 
Cardy-Verlinde formulae for CFTs with AdS duals in
   Einstein gravity 

Now consider a critical brane moving in a black hole bulk, in Einstein
gravity. When it is near the AdS boundary, the
CFT on the brane obeys the following Cardy-Verlinde formula,
