Cardy-Verlinde formulae for CFTs with AdS duals in
   Gauss-Bonnet gravity 

Now consider the case of the critical brane moving in a Gauss-Bonnet
black hole bulk. For the brane near the AdS boundary we have a
holographic description, but not otherwise. We shall now derive the
Cardy-Verlinde formula for the CFT on the brane, when the holographic
description holds.

The entropy of the CFT is just given by the total entropy of the two
Gauss-Bonnet black holes ,
S=2._n-2 Z_H^n-2  4 G_n  [1+2
(n-2 n-4 ) Z_H^2  ].
Note that the Gauss-Bonnet black hole entropy does not obey the area
law which exists in Einstein gravity. The temperature of the CFT is
given by the temperature of the black hole, , with the
appropriate redshift factor, ,
T=T_BH  k_eff Z , where  T_BH =h_BH  '(Z_H) 4 .
